So this seems like a bug in a dusty corner of things... I'm writing a syntax extension [here](https://github.com/killerswan/ovid/blob/33bb99247fa5a62194d32ede9d342b0235371172/CSVProvider.rs).

At some point in that, I'm trying to define a line to use in a struct:

```
   let col = quote_item!(icx,
      pub $col0: String
   ).expect("Should be able to label a sample column (for use inside a struct def)");

   let item0 = quote_item!(icx,
      pub struct $MyCsvRow {
         $col,
      }
   );
```

Now that may be wrong in the first place (there's [an error](https://gist.github.com/killerswan/98486086d32a3fad001a) on mismatched `pub`s), but what's more interesting is that when I remove the `pub` from that first quote (line 215), I get a syntax-extension-level-ICE:

```
error: internal compiler error: unexpected failure
note: the compiler hit an unexpected failure path. this is a bug.
note: we would appreciate a bug report: http://doc.rust-lang.org/complement-bugreport.html
note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` for a backtrace
task 'rustc' failed at 'Should be able to label a sample column (for use inside a struct def)', /Users/kevin/code/rust/src/libcore/option.rs:251
```

As though using `quote_item!` to make `pub Verse: String` is valid,  but `Verse: String` is invalid...
